  "prompt": "My Upwork account is suspended. What should I do now?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to address an Upwork account suspension:\n\n1. Review the suspension notice\n- Check the specific reason for suspension\n- Look for details in your email or Upwork account\n\n2. Contact Upwork Support\n- Submit a support ticket explaining your situation\n- Request details about the suspension\n- Be professional and cooperative\n\n3. Potential resolution strategies\n- If policy violation: Understand and address the specific issue\n- If payment/verification problem: Resolve outstanding requirements\n- If account irregularities: Provide requested documentation\n\n4. Gather supporting documentation\n- Proof of identity\n- Work history\n- Communication records\n- Any relevant documentation\n\n5. Wait for Upwork's response\n- Response times vary\n- Follow their instructions carefully\n- Be patient and persistent\n\n6. Consider alternatives if suspension is permanent\n- Appeal the decision\n- Explore other freelancing platforms like Freelancer, Fiverr, etc.\n\n7. Prevent future suspensions\n- Carefully read and follow Upwork's terms of service\n- Maintain professional communication\n- Keep your profile and work history clean\n\nRemember, each suspension case is unique, so the specific approach may vary depending on the circumstances.\n\nWould you like help drafting a support ticket or discussing your specific situation?",
